Today was loads, yes loads, of awesome.  I woke up really early, and fell back asleep, but then mom woke me up again and i stumbled off to the shower, crying, ok not really, but it adds some spice.  So mom leaves this morning and i tell my sister that she has to wait for me after school because i have to serve my detention.  Anyways we go to school, and of course as soon as my car stops Michelle jumps out like a parachuteist getting out of a c-130 in the heat of battle.  But its cool because i dont really want people thinking that im sitting in the car with a prostitute anyways.  So i hang out in the lot with Andrew and Ryan and we all listen to some awesome music on my stereo system (which sucks because the base is all blown out) but its ok for just killing time.  So school starts and yadda yadda yadda.  Oh yeah, after first period we had activity period today, and no-one in first period chose to tell me about it because i just got up and left when the bell rang and headed off to second period.  When i get there Mrs. Riley is like, "Adam, you realize this is activity period right?" so im like "Damn" and i head off back to first period.  When i get there everyone is laughing at me so i issue a nice "Fuck you guys" and its all good again.  Oh, and i saw almost the funniest thing i have ever seen in my life yesterday, not kidding, it was the FUNNIEST thing EVER.  This kid in my second period class, Tim, well, hes literally mentally retarded, but its cool and all, its not like everyone makes fun of him.  He just plays with the clay and we basically leave him alone.  So he has the hotts for this one girl in our class, and shes "normal" and he obviously likes her. Basically everyday he will walk up behind her and grunt a little and smile real big at her and shes like "Good job Tim, now go sit down" so he walks away.  But yesterday was different, he walks up behind her and grunts a little, she says her normal "Go sit down Tim" and he just keeps standing there.  Then his finger slowly moves to his nose and he picks out a huge buger.  And literally in slow motion he moves it toward the girl and she is utterly terrifyied, shure enough he rubs it off on her jacket, grunts a little more and smiles, then he soes and sits down.  I, as did almost the rest of the class, almost shit my pants.  So anyways back to today.  School got out and i head off towards my detention in Cassaros room, and i was very weird because i was the only kid in there, and hes obviously at least a little gay, and he kept making wise ass remarks.  So finally im like "My sister is waiting for me in the parking lot, ive got to go give her a ride home" so hes like "if you want to get started with me ill just give you a refferal" and i was like "go ahead, im just telling you i have to give her a ride home, she cant just wander the campus" so he let me go early.  So on my way home Katy calls me and shes all like "I was supposed to pick you up at 2:15 and your not home, im in your driveway"  So i was like "well im on my way ho-......" thats when i dropped the phone because i had to do a but load of shifting. So i get home and theres Katy sitting in my driveway all revving her engine and yelling at me for not getting home early enough, ok she didnt yell.  So her and i are headed to the thrift store to find me a trench coat for this skit thing im doing with micheal and the other scout kids, its based on Jay and Silent bob, so i needed a green trench coat.  Anyways we go there and KT is like oh god we gotta go check out the kids shirt section, which is apparently where every emo kid on the planet gets his clothing because they were like tight little kids clothes, but i have to admit they were pretty cool.  Anyways we were looking through the shirts for like 20 minutes when this little kid comes up and starts going through them, so im like hey dude check this one out and i hold up a shirt that says "i quit having sex for bowling" and he just stared at it blank eyed then he went back to looking at shirts.  so KT and i had a good laugh then like 3 min later he holds up this shirt and says to me "hey kid i found a gay boys shirt for you" i just laughed uncontrolably as did KT, so the kids all proud of himself until im like "dude that says Calvin Klien, and hes not gay" so we argued for like 4 minutes while KT watched and laughed and finally im like "dude your 6 years old, im like 10 years older than you, I win." so he stomps off to find his mom. So Katy and i finish our shopping and we go over to mens to find a trench coat, we get a shitty green one and head off towards the cash registers.  By this time that little shit has had enough time to go find a girls sweater and he walks up behind me, hits me, and holds up the jacket sweater thing and says i bet you would like this gay boy.  So i was like "wow, dude thats perfect" I took it from him and tried it on, it was really tight and emo looking, i did feel a little gay but it was funny because the kid was obviously mad thinking that he had helped me out so he finally stomps off and KT and I continue to laugh.  So we leave the thrift place and Kt is like omfg, if i take you home im going to miss my spanish class, so i make her call my mom, and long story short im going to go to spanish class with her.  so we have like an hour to kill in fort myers, and around this time i get around to telling the aforementioned retard story, which about makes KT crap herself, which is bad because shes driving.  anyways we go to the BK lounge and get some fries and burgers, and yeah, i love fries.  so then we head off to spanish class over there at edison and we get there early, so were developing a plan to get me into her class.  I honestly liked the idea of playing a retarded half brother that she had to care for, but she didnt like that one, so we went with me being her really hot brother, i added the really hot part.  So we walk around and she gives me a campus tour, which sucks a little because she really has no idea where she is, but i did find out her favorite place to tie her shoe, and im not kidding she seriously has a favorite place to tie her shoe.  So class is about to begin and she checks her messages and calls one of em back and shes like im here hanging out with adam number three, yada yada.  Of course i dwelt on the Adam three part, it made me kinda sad inside, mostly because i'm pretty shure i'm the Adam thats known her the longest.  So i get the whole story and aparently im really Adam number two (just behind dispenza) but to the outside world im three because this other adam would feel bad, because she once said adam two (me) was a good friend, and this other adam was like "it makes me feel good to know im one of your best friends" and she couldnt cut him down after saying something like that.  its almost as effed up as math, lmao inside joke there kids.  Anyways we go to class and i have no idea whats going on, and im pretty shure Katy dosent either because she is basically writing notes back and forth to me in her textbook but it was good times all around, and after class we booked it outta there. then i went home and thats basically it, im shure i left out a lot but there is so much to remember you know... till next time.
-Adam

This week is starting out on a good foot, well its not really a good foot, but a necessary one.  My girlfriend and I have started a "break" (I think), but I'm not positive.  I mean, everything is cool and all, but when my friend asked what was wrong when we werent holding hands, or talking much, she said "We're just friends," and that really hurts to hear, to be honest I'm not sure if that constitutes a "break" or a "break-up." I hope to god its not the latter of the two.  But I completely understand why we need time apart, I can't really tell the whole story, because its not yours to know.  Just understand that I'm a willing participant in this break, it will make it better for her, although it will only eat me up inside.  And don't think that I don't understand that she is being eaten up inside by all the things that she feels right now, its not all about me.  So, this will be my last post until we are back together, because I will only get myself going more and more by putting it into words.  And for those who think that I'm acting cold or heartless, because thats how I feel I'm coming off, just know that I cant express how I'm feeling without getting myself into an emotional breakdown and becoming unproductive in anything, and I know that that is not what she wants to happen, because that is why I'm allowing this to happen between us, I dont want that to happen to her, so I'm holding on for her.  And it dosent help really that everyone who knows her is telling me all these things like "She'll never go back to you," "I can't see how she will get with you a second time," etc.  To tell you the truth people, I don't want to hear it anymore.  Maybe I'm just getting off track, and it really is just a break, but it feels so much like the end.  Deep down inside I know it isn't though.  And thats the only thread I have to hold onto, so don't tell me its a false impression.
